---
description: Protect site env vars and secrets from accidental wipes on unrelated saves
globs:
  - frontend/app/sites/**/*.tsx
  - frontend/lib/api.ts
  - backend/internal/sites/service.go
  - backend/internal/secrets/**
---

# Env vars and secrets

- **Never** wipe-and-replace all env vars on every site settings save. Use merge/upsert on the backend; on the frontend send `env_vars` only when that section was edited (`envVarsDirty`).
- Env var and secret **names** must always be visible in the UI (labels + placeholders). Never bind only the value field.
- API JSON uses lowercase `key` / `value`. When reading responses, normalize with `normalizeEnvVar` / `normalizeSecretMeta` (accept legacy `Key` too).
- Reject saving env vars with a value but no name. Do not `DELETE FROM site_env_vars` for the whole site on PATCH unless replacing with a validated full list.
- Secrets: require non-empty trimmed keys; do not hide list rows with empty keys — fix data via migration instead.
